## On cutting sausages

I made a [quick sausage lasagne][sausage-lasagne] for the first time using [cauldron vegetarian sausages][vege-sausages].  It turned out well enough, but the difference between meat and plant based sausages is in how they deform under heat.  The meat ones crumble away and you get a even ragu, the plant ones remain the size you cut them up into, which makes for a very chunky ragu and uneven layers in the lasagne.  Really just sharing this as an aide-memoire for next time that, unlike my usual rustic style in the kitchen, the vegetarian sausages need to be more carefully cut into much smaller chunks.

